  "text": "The Kubernetes API server implements a multi-layer authentication chain in kubernetes/kubernetes. The main orchestration happens in pkg/kubeapiserver/authenticator/config.go, where the Config.New() method constructs the complete authentication chain by assembling multiple authenticators.\n\nRequest-level authenticators are used to extract authentication information from HTTP requests:\n- Anonymous authenticator (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/request/anonymous/anonymous.go) provides fallback anonymous authentication when enabled\n- Bearer token authenticator (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/request/bearertoken/bearertoken.go) extracts bearer tokens from Authorization headers\n- X509/Client certificate authenticator (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/request/x509/x509.go) verifies client certificates and extracts user information from certificate attributes\n- Request header authenticator (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/request/headerrequest/requestheader.go) supports front-proxy style authentication\n- Websocket authenticator (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/request/websocket/protocol.go) handles WebSocket-specific authentication\n- Union authenticator (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/request/union/union.go) chains multiple request authenticators together\n\nToken-level authenticators verify bearer tokens:\n- Service account JWT authenticator (pkg/serviceaccount/jwt.go) uses JWTTokenAuthenticator() function to verify service account tokens with configurable issuers and validators\n- Legacy service account validator (pkg/serviceaccount/legacy.go) with NewLegacyValidator() maintains backwards compatibility for secret-based tokens\n- Token file authenticator (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/token/tokenfile/tokenfile.go) reads static tokens from CSV files via NewCSV()\n- Token union authenticator (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/token/union/union.go) chains multiple token authenticators\n- Token cache (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/token/cache/cached_token_authenticator.go) wraps token authenticators with caching via New()\n- JWT token authenticator (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/token/jwt/jwt.go) handles generic JWT validation\n\nThe chain construction (Config.New() in pkg/kubeapiserver/authenticator/config.go) orchestrates these authenticators in the following order: request headers (front proxy), X509 certificates, bearer tokens (which includes token file, service account tokens, and webhook tokens), and finally anonymous authentication as a fallback. Supporting interfaces are defined in staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/authenticator/interfaces.go."
